description:
Overview:

This opportunity is for a Senior Data Engineer / Tech Lead-level profile with strong hands-on experience in modern data engineering, cloud platforms, and data architecture.

What are we looking for?

At least 5 years as a Data Engineer;
Experience with SQL & Python;
Vast experience with Databricks;
Vast experience with ETL and ELT, CI/CD tools;
Experience with Cloud;
Have a strong understanding of different data modeling methodologies (Kimball, Inmon, Data Vault);
Experience with DBT, Airflow & Spark using tools like Tableau, Spotfire, Power BI, etc;
Experience with search tools (plus);
Experience with Data Governance and Medallion Architecture are a plus.

What can you expect from us?

A permanent job contract for a long term project;
Tech equipment + SIM Card + personal smartphone;
Health and Life Insurance;
Social events and team buildings;
The commitment of letting you grow with us, and be rewarded accordingly;
A dynamic and young team that will be always there to support you;
Training in the latest technologies;
Coffee, fruits, snacks and a warm welcoming when you pass by the office.

We're looking for a Data Engineer to join Wildlife's Analytics & Insights team.

Wildlife is one of the largest mobile gaming companies in the world. Behind every game we ship, there's a data infrastructure that tells us how players behave, how much revenue each title is generating, and how the operation is performing day to day.

As a Data Engineer on the Analytics & Insights team, you'll work on the core products and platform that make this data trustworthy and available to everyone who depends on it, from game teams, marketing operations, and data scientists. Some of the challenges you'll work on:

Support the decision-making of our games operations through high-quality data products and well-structured dashboards;
Building and evolving integrations with third-party APIs, such as app stores, ad networks, and other external data providers;
Developing our internal event streaming process, responsible for the analytical and backend events;
Designing and maintaining the pipelines and tables that power our revenue, player, KPI, crashlytics, and experimentation data;
Operating and evolving the data platform itself, including Airflow, Databricks workspace, data lake, and Looker.

We know the work we do has a high impact on the company's success. The right person for this role is naturally curious, comfortable taking the initiative, loves solving problems end-to-end, and can thrive in a fast and growing business.


What you'll do

Solve open-ended problems that directly affect how the company tracks revenue, players, and game performance;
Take projects end-to-end — design, build, ship, and own them in production, with support from senior engineers on the team;
Work cross-functionally with Data Engineers in other teams, Data Scientists, Game Engineers, SDK Engineers, UA Analysts, and Game Ops;
Help improve the availability, reliability, performance, and cost of our existing systems — not just ship new features on top of them.

What you'll need

Solid Python and SQL skills;
Hands-on experience with data engineering tools and concepts, such as ingestion services, orchestration, batch and streaming processing, data lakes, BI concepts;
Ownership mindset for the projects you work on;
Great communication skills;
Proficiency in written English.

Main challenges

The team is responsible for designing, building, and evolving a wide set of complex data products, including ingestion (batch and streaming), pipelines, BI, data quality, and the infrastructure underneath all of it. Trade-offs are constant.
We integrate with several external APIs (app stores, ad networks, pricing providers) and internal event sources, each with its own quirks.
Our outputs feed business-critical decisions, so reliability and data quality are very important.
It's a deeply cross-functional environment — you'll interact with Data Engineers in other teams, Data Scientists, Game Engineers, SDK Engineers, UA Analysts, and Game Ops.

As a Data Engineer on the team, you'll help us keep the systems we build available, reliable, performant, cost-effective, and maintainable as the scope keeps growing.


More about you

You're impact-driven and curious about adjacent disciplines (backend, data science, platform, infrastructure);
You like open-ended problems and are comfortable when the answer isn't obvious;
You communicate in a structured way, in writing and in conversation;
You raise the bar for the people around you, not just for yourself.

About Wildlife

Wildlife is one of the world's leading mobile game developers and publishers. We have released more than 60 titles, reaching billions of people around the globe. Here, we create games that excite, intrigue, and engage our players for years to come.



Equal Opportunity

Wildlife is proud to be an Equal Opportunity and Affirmative Action employer. We do not discriminate based on race, color, national origin, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, protected veteran status, disability, age, or other applicable legally protected characteristics. We also consider qualified applicants with criminal histories, consistent with applicable federal, state, and local law.

Viva.com, the 1st Tech Bank in Europe for Businesses, revolutionises omnichannel payments acceptance, offers card issuing, loans and deposit accounts. Viva.com is the first to pioneer and holds the top position in the Tap on Any Device technology, enabling payments acceptance on any device or even without a device.

Today Viva.com is leading the transition to All-in-One business solutions, powered by its full suite of financial services. To that end, reflecting its holistic approach to business needs, Viva.com has built a dynamic ecosystem featuring over 450 tech partner-innovators in the software and hardware space. Connecting directly to all local payment schemes, alternative payment methods and payment systems across the continent, further strengthens Viva.com’s value proposition. 

Viva.com envisions to provide businesses a value-driven platform to accelerate the adoption of the latest technology. 

The Role

As a DevOps Engineer, you will play a key role in designing, implementing, and improving the automation, deployment, observability, and operational capabilities that support Viva.com’s technology platforms.

You will work closely with engineering, cloud infrastructure, SRE, architecture, QA, security, and operations teams to enable reliable software delivery, scalable cloud-native infrastructure, and efficient production operations.

This role requires a self-driven engineer with strong ownership, technical curiosity, and a continuous improvement mindset. You will be expected to work autonomously, identify areas for optimization, challenge existing processes, and actively contribute to the evolution of our DevOps practices.

A strong focus will be placed on Azure DevOps, AKS, CI/CD automation, Infrastructure-as-Code, Datadog observability, cloud-native operations, and AI-assisted automation.

Responsibilities: 

Design, implement, maintain, and continuously improve CI/CD pipelines across multiple applications, services, and environments;
Support and enhance deployment automation using Azure DevOps, YAML pipelines, scripting, templates, and reusable pipeline components;
Contribute to the migration, operation, and optimization of workloads running on Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS) and other cloud-native platforms;
Build, maintain, and improve Infrastructure-as-Code practices to support repeatable, secure, and scalable infrastructure delivery;
Automate manual and repetitive operational tasks using scripting, tooling, and where applicable, AI-assisted automation capabilities;
Support the standardization and continuous improvement of release management, deployment governance, and production delivery processes;
Implement and maintain observability capabilities using Datadog, including monitors, dashboards, logs, metrics, alerts, and integrations;
Collaborate with SRE and engineering teams to improve system reliability, incident detection, alert quality, and operational visibility;
Proactively identify performance, scalability, reliability, and cost optimization opportunities across infrastructure and delivery workflows;
Participate in the design and implementation of cloud-native solutions with a focus on resilience, maintainability, automation, and operational excellence;
Research, evaluate, and introduce emerging technologies, including AI-powered DevOps, observability, automation, and incident response tooling;
Work closely with development, QA, infrastructure, security, and operations teams to enable efficient end-to-end delivery;
Contribute to technical documentation, operational runbooks, deployment guides, and knowledge-sharing practices;
Take ownership of assigned initiatives and drive them independently from analysis and implementation through validation and operational handover.

At Viva.com, we believe in amplifying human potential through AI. When you join us, you're stepping into a future-forward environment where technology empowers every role, driving smarter, more efficient. 

Requirements

Bachelor's/Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Technology, or equivalent proven professional experience;
At least 2 years of hands-on experience in a DevOps Engineer, Cloud Engineer, Platform Engineer, or similar role;
Strong hands-on experience with Microsoft Azure, including resource deployment, configuration, monitoring, and operational management;
Practical experience with Azure DevOps, CI/CD pipelines, repositories, service connections, artifacts, and release automation;
Good understanding of Kubernetes, preferably with hands-on experience in Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS);
Experience with containerization technologies such as Docker and container orchestration platforms such as Kubernetes, AKS, OpenShift, or similar;
Experience with Infrastructure-as-Code concepts and tools such as ARM templates, Bicep, Terraform, or similar;
Solid scripting skills using PowerShell, Bash/Shell, or Python, experience with Windows and Linux server administration;
Familiarity with monitorin

Quer fazer parte de um time que cria oportunidades e potencializa a evolução?

 

Como alcançamos tudo isso?

Através de um ecossistema de mais de 12 mil pessoas inconformadas que, juntas, oferecem soluções, produtos e educam o mercado. Atuamos como uma Única TOTVS, integrando diferentes soluções e expertises para educar o mercado e simplificar o mundo dos negócios. Para nós, a evolução é constante e acontece de gente para gente: usamos nossa inquietude para antecipar tendências e transformar o crescimento real da tecnologia.


Nosso jeito de ser:

🤖IH + IA (Inteligência Humana + Inteligência Artificial): Acreditamos que a tecnologia potencializa, mas as pessoas direcionam. Aqui, a IA nos dá escala e eficiência, enquanto a nossa Inteligência Humana traz a estratégia, o contexto e o cuidado. É essa combinação que nos permite criar soluções inovadoras com um propósito real.

🚀Protagonismo e Evolução: Somos movidos pelo aprendizado contínuo e pela coragem de assumir o comando da própria carreira. Aqui, incentivamos a inquietude e oferecemos o ambiente fértil para quem quer crescer, criar e se transformar.

Resultado Responsável: Valorizamos a liberdade para agir e a responsabilidade com o todo. Aqui, você tem voz para desafiar o status quo e autonomia para buscar resultados que gerem valor real para nossos clientes e para a sociedade.

🧘🏼‍♀️Bem-Estar Integral: Cuidamos de quem faz a evolução acontecer. Buscamos o bem-estar integral de cada pessoa colaboradora, por meio de ações e benefícios que viabilizam recursos de autocuidado através de 5 pilares: Emocional, Financeiro, Físico, Ocupacional e Social.

🫂Pluralidade e Pertencimento: A diversidade é o que nos torna potentes. Promovemos a inclusão e o pertencimento de forma ativa, garantindo que a TOTVS seja um lugar onde você pode ser quem você é. Nossa expertise é humana e viva: acolhemos as diferenças para empoderar negócios dentro e fora da empresa.

Desafio do time

Você fará parte do time de produto do RD Vendas, atuando na construção e evolução da jornada de pré-vendas dentro do produto. Seu desafio será apoiar na identificação de oportunidades de melhoria, estruturar soluções de forma colaborativa e garantir a entrega de valor para os clientes, trabalhando próximo de engenharia, design e stakeholders.

Principais entregas
Apoiar na identificação de problemas e oportunidades a partir de dados, feedbacks de clientes e contexto do produto;
Contribuir na definição e evolução de funcionalidades do CRM, especialmente relacionadas à jornada de pré-vendas;
Acompanhar o desenvolvimento das iniciativas junto ao time de engenharia, garantindo alinhamento e clareza de escopo;
Participar da validação de entregas, garantindo qualidade e aderência ao problema proposto;
Monitorar métricas e indicadores das funcionalidades, apoiando na análise de impacto;
Comunicar o andamento das iniciativas e resultados para o time e stakeholders.
Perfil que buscamos
Interesse em atuar com produto digital, com vontade de aprender e se desenvolver na área;
Boa capacidade analítica e de organização para lidar com problemas e informações;
Habilidade de comunicação clara e colaboração com diferentes áreas;
Postura aberta a feedbacks e aprendizado contínuo;
Capacidade de priorização e senso de responsabilidade com entregas;
Interesse em entender o cliente e o impacto das soluções no negócio.
Será considerado um diferencial
Experiência prévia (mesmo que inicial) com produto, tecnologia ou áreas correlatas como CS ou Suporte;
Conhecimento básico em métricas de produto ou análise de dados;
Familiaridade com metodologias ágeis;
Interesse por temas como CRM, vendas e pré-vendas;
Experiência com ferramentas como Mixpanel, Excel/Sheets ou similares.

 

Etapas do processo seletivo:

Aplicação - Envio da inscrição;
Mindsight – Teste de estilo de trabalho;
Talent Acquisition - Entrevista por competência com o time de recrutamento;
Entrevista Técnica - Entrevista técnica para discussão de requisitos da vaga;
Entrevista Final - Conversa final com a gerência para alinhamento;
Offer - Fase de conclusão do processo seletivo, com a apresentação da proposta de trabalho.

Obs: Podem ter etapas complementares e/ou alterações, de acordo com a necessidade do processo.

 

 

 

🔒 Nos comprometemos com a segurança dos seus dados! Em nosso Aviso de Privacidade, descrevemos quais dados coletamos, como são consumidos e armazenados, em conformidade com a LGPD.



Se você é uma pessoa movida por desafios, criatividade e impacto genuíno, avance conosco nessa jornada de evolução!
Faça parte do nosso time!
